    },
    {
      "id": "7504221c_2bbb7703",
      "file_path": "openecomp-be/backend/openecomp-sdc-vendor-software-product-manager/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/vendorsoftwareproduct/security/SecurityManager.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 170,
      "message": "I would recommend splinting reading certificates on to two methods, one that read package cert and one that reads trusted certs. That way the initialization at the beginning will be unnecessary and methods that return cert will not change trustedCertificateFromPackage \"silently\". It would be something like this:\n\nif(packageCerts == null) {\n    cert = readPackageCertFromCms(...)\n    trustedCertificateFromPackage = readTrustedCertFromCms(...)\n} else {\n    cert = readPackageCertFromPackage(...)\n    trustedCertificateFromPackage = readTrustedCertFromPackage(...)\n}",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5098,
        "name": "Bartosz Gardziejewski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "bartosz.gardziejewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "BartoszG"
      },
      "updated": "2021-01-15 08:30:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
